text.tspan: Figure 7: Parameter Ranges and Effects on Shedding
These six panels are for the cell-to-cell spread model using the mean values
of the variables across participants with at least 1 positive swab. The first pair is for
the log killing rate (A) and its effect on median HHV8 log viral load (B). The next is for
log viral production rate (C) and its effect on the same measure (D). The last pair
are for log reactivation rate from latency (E) and its effect on percent positive swabs (F).
